🧠 1. What are Lock-Free and Wait-Free Algorithms?

These are non-blocking algorithms—they avoid traditional locks.

👉 Built using:

CAS (Compare-And-Swap)
Atomic variables
Memory visibility guarantees

🔓 2. Lock-Free Algorithm
👉 Definition

    At least one thread always makes progress, even if others are stuck.

    ✔ Key Idea
        Threads may retry
        Some threads may starve
        But system as a whole never stops

🔁 How it works
    Read value
    Try CAS update
    If fails → retry

👉 This retry loop = spin

⚠️ Problem
One unlucky thread may retry forever → starvation possible


🚀 3. Wait-Free Algorithm
👉 Definition

    Every thread finishes in a bounded number of steps

    ✔ Key Idea
        No starvation
        Guaranteed completion
        Strongest guarantee

🔁 Why this is Wait-Free?
    Each thread writes to its own slot
    No contention
    No retries
    Guaranteed progress

⚔️ 4. Lock-Free vs Wait-Free
Feature	                Lock-Free	    Wait-Free
Progress                guarantee	    System-wide	Per-thread
Starvation	            Possible	    Impossible
Complexity	            Medium	        Very high
Performance	            High	        Very high (but costly design)

🧠 5. CAS (Core of Both Lock-free and wait-free)

All of this depends on:

compareAndSet(expected, newValue)

👉 Behavior
If value == expected → update
Else → fail

👉 Atomic hardware instruction


